# Celestial Blueprint

A tiered, interrogation-driven planning system for CHAOS_DAO_FORGE. Dōng Quān-guided. API-first. Usable by any agent, tool, or automation.

## Architecture

```
backend/        FastAPI service — the shared engine all clients call
frontend/       React + React Flow canvas — the first client
skill/          SKILL.md — methodology for any agent (day-1 usable, no backend needed)
docs/           FORMAT.md, API.md, tier templates, prompt-packs
blueprints/     Active blueprint markdown files (portable, git-tracked)
chronicles/     CHRONICLE RAW + CYCLE captures
```

## API-First Principle

All planning logic lives in the backend behind a documented REST API. The React canvas, CLI (Stage 3), and MCP server (Stage 4) are all thin clients of the same API. Nothing is throwaway.

## 6-Stage Roadmap

| Stage | Name | What |
|-------|------|------|
| 1 | The Forge | Web app — backend API + React canvas |
| 2 | The Summoning | System agent discovery + model routing |
| 3 | The Hands | CLI + automation tools |
| 4 | The Nerves | MCP layer (any-agent integration) |
| 5 | The Brain | Persistent intelligence + project connection |
| 6 | The Ascension | OS integration |

## Quick Start (Phase 1)

```bash
# Backend
cd backend && python -m venv .venv && source .venv/bin/activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
uvicorn app.main:app --reload

# Frontend
cd frontend && npm install && npm run dev
```

## Methodology Skill (day-1, no backend needed)

The `skill/celestial-blueprint/SKILL.md` encodes the full planning methodology — 4 tiers, Dōng Quān 6-step interrogation, chronicle protocol. Usable in Claude Code, OpenCode, or any agent that loads skills, with or without the backend running.

## Blueprint Format

See `docs/FORMAT.md`. Blueprints are portable markdown files (YAML frontmatter + sectioned body) that round-trip to JSON and SQLite. Git-tracked. Obsidian-readable.
